From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 01:23:22 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: pin deferred hot/cold-on-template-fields behavior

Documents the current v1 limitation: hot/cold markers on a compact class template are ignored for instantiations (padding-min only), while atomic isolation still applies. Mega<int> places d first by alignment, not the hot value. Flip this test when hot/cold-on-template-fields is implemented. Ground truth from the layout dump.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-template-hotcold-deferred.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-template-hotcold-deferred.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..b99cd7a67
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-template-hotcold-deferred.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@
+// DOCUMENTED LIMITATION (pins current behavior; flip when implemented): hot/cold
+// markers on a compact TEMPLATE's fields are currently IGNORED for instantiations
+// -- the per-instantiation reorder is padding-min only. Atomic isolation DOES
+// still apply. The non-template form honors hot/cold (compact-all-features-
+// torture.cpp), so here `value` is NOT pulled first despite being `hot`.
+//
+// Source {tag(cold), value(hot), refs(_Atomic), d}. Mega<int> reorders by
+// alignment only -> {d, value, refs, tag}, with refs isolated to its own line.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -fdump-record-layouts %s | FileCheck %s
+
+template <class T> compact struct Mega {
+  cold char tag;
+  hot T value;
+  _Atomic int refs;
+  double d;
+};
+
+Mega<int> m;
+
+static_assert(sizeof(Mega<int>) == 192, "padding-min + atomic isolation");
+
+// d is first (alignment), NOT value -- confirming hot is ignored for templates:
+// CHECK:      struct Mega<int>
+// CHECK:      0 |{{.*}}double d
+// CHECK:      8 |{{.*}}int value
+// CHECK:      64 |{{.*}}refs
+// CHECK:      128 |{{.*}}char tag
